According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Children Cosmetics market was valued at USD 14.52 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 15.18 billion in 2025 to USD 19.67 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.5% during the forecast period. The market is expanding steadily as parents increasingly seek child-safe, dermatologist-tested, and organic personal care products that prioritize skin health while offering age-appropriate formulations and engaging product designs.
